  "body": "**What happened**\r\n\r\nUsing OpenID Connect as an authentication provider with a client-secret that contains a special character like the `+` sign leads to refresh tokens not working because `kubectl` doesn't URL encode the client-secret before base64-encoding the basic auth header.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**\r\n\r\n`kubectl` should URL encode the client-secret as per the OAuth2 spec.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**\r\n\r\nSet up an OIDC auth with a `+` in the client secret.\r\n\r\n**Environment**\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): all versions have this bug.\r\n\r\n**Discussion**\r\n\r\nI first filed this against Go (golang/go#31577) but it turns out that the URL encoding is only specified for OAuth2, not in the general case.\r\n\r\nBefore calling [`req.SetBasicAuth(user, pass)`](https://golang.org/pkg/net/http/#Request.SetBasicAuth) the arguments must be URL encoded.\r\n\r\nSee Go's own OAuth2 implementation, which had this same bug until golang/oauth2#237 fixed it.",
